caller_intent: Harvey Dillon wanted to confirm the discount percentage he received for paying his insurance premiums in full, specifically for his auto and homeowners policies.
resolution_steps: Heather checked the auto policy and confirmed a $196 paid-in-full discount, noting the premium after discount was $1,782.49.
Heather explained the auto policy's $5 discount might be from a 'green discount' (paperless enrollment) or payment method.
Heather reviewed the homeowners policy, noting a $200+ discount but confusion about whether recent changes (endorsement #630) affected the premium calculation.
Heather advised Harvey to check the 'renewing' section on his policy portal for details.
knowledge_required: Understanding of insurance discounts (paid-in-full, green/paperless, endorsement changes)
Ability to access and interpret policy details via carrier systems (Auto Owners)
Familiarity with premium calculation logic and policy portal navigation
summary: Harvey called to confirm discounts from paying insurance premiums in full. Heather verified a $196 auto discount and $200+ homeowners discount but noted confusion about recent policy changes. The call concluded with Heather guiding Harvey to check his policy portal for detailed breakdowns.
